# Role Manual (Current Build)

## Global Rules
- Turn choice: `Draw` or `Use Skill`.
- Event cards are unique draw: each card is drawn once from deck.
- Finn purchase restriction:
  - Finn cannot buy anything by default (trade/food).
  - Volunteer help on Finn grants `1` assisted-buy chance.
  - Each successful Finn purchase consumes `1` assisted-buy chance.
- Finn photo rule:
  - Finn cannot refuse being photographed.
  - Same tourist can photograph Finn at most once.
- Photo reward:
  - Target of photo gains `+1 product` (photo item).
- Performance watcher reward:
  - Watch flow order:
  - First choose to watch.
  - Then pay one watch cost.
  - Then optionally toggle orange wear (`👑 <-> 🤴🏻`).
  - Watcher must choose one watch cost:
  - pay `💰-1`, or pay `🔍-2`.
  - Performer gains `💰+1` from each watcher.
  - Watcher can choose to toggle orange wear status while watching:
  - `👑 -> 🤴🏻` (wear) or `🤴🏻 -> 👑` (take off).

---

## 1) Finn
- Initial: `🔍2 💰0 ❤️3 📦0 👑0 🤴🏻0`
- Draw cost: `THEN / stamina-1 | curiosity-1` (auto takes first payable option).
- Skill: ask one player with orange item; if accepted, Finn wears `+1` orange and gains `⭐️+1`.
- Progress rule: Finn `⭐️` is always equal to current worn orange count (`🤴🏻`).
- Win: wear `3` orange items (`🤴🏻 >= 3`).
- Auto strategy (synced to game logic):
  - Turn choice: prefer `Use Skill`; if no skill value, then `Draw`.
  - Draw payment: normally pay `❤️`; switch to `🔍` when `❤️ <= 1`.
  - Target selection: prioritize players closest to winning; tie-break by lower orange stock.
  - Consent policy: if another player asks Finn-side consent to help Finn wear, default `Refuse` when refusal is allowed.
  - Watching performance:
    - Prefer to watch if it can trigger wear (`👑 -> 🤴🏻`) or if `🔍 <= 1`.
    - Prefer paying watch cost by `💰`, fallback to `🔍`.
  - Card choices:
    - Prefer choices that convert current `👑` into worn progress until `🤴🏻=3`.
    - On card 8 item choice, prefer `📦` over extra `👑` to avoid dead stock.

## 2) Tourist
- Initial: `🔍2 💰6 ❤️4 📦1 👑0 🤴🏻0`
- Draw cost: `OR / money-1 | curiosity-1`
- Skill: choose target and request photo consent (Finn is forced-consent).
  - On shoot: tourist pays `💰-1 ❤️-1`, target gets `📦+1`.
  - Valid photo only if target is wearing orange (`🤴🏻 > 0`), then tourist gains `⭐️+1`.
- Win: `3` valid photos (same tourist can photo Finn only once).
- Auto strategy (synced to game logic):
  - Turn choice: skill-first if a valid photo line exists; otherwise draw.
  - Draw payment: strongly prefer spending `🔍` over `💰`.
  - Photo targeting: prioritize `🤴🏻` target first, then orange-related targets.
  - Consent policy: if target can refuse a tourist photo/request, default `Refuse`.
  - Watching payment: mostly pay `💰`, fallback `🔍`.

## 3) Vendor
- Initial: `🔍2 💰0 ❤️6 📦2 👑1 🤴🏻0`
- Draw cost: `THEN / stamina-1 | money-1`
- Skill: sell one item to one buyer (buyer may accept/refuse).
  - Normal item base price: `1`
  - Orange item base price: `2`
  - Event effect may add orange price bonus.
- Win: `3` valid trades.
- Auto strategy (synced to game logic):
  - Turn choice: trade-first when there are likely buyers; otherwise draw.
  - Trade item: choose item by expected successful buyers and price yield.
  - Trade partner: prefer targets with purchase capability and lower refusal risk.
  - Refuse policy: limited anti-leader refusal (low-medium probability).
  - Watching payment: prefer `💰`, fallback `🔍`.

## 4) Food Vendor
- Initial: `🔍3 💰0 ❤️1 📦0 👑0 🤴🏻0`
- Draw cost: `THEN / curiosity-1`
- Skill: start food offering to all players (including self), one by one.
  - Start requirement: `❤️ >= 2`
  - Buyer condition: `🔍 >= 2` and can pay `💰1` (self does not pay).
  - Buyer effect: `❤️ +1` (may be multiplied by event effect).
  - End-of-offer stamina cost:
    - no buyer: `❤️ -1`
    - >=1 buyer: `❤️ -2`
    - may be multiplied by event effect.
- Win: `5` successful servings total.
  - Self-serving is counted at most once.
- Auto strategy (synced to game logic):
  - Turn choice: supply-first when start condition is met (`❤️>=2`); otherwise draw.
  - Supply accept/deny: accept when buyer-side payment is feasible; slight anti-leader suppression.
  - Event target choice: threat-aware targeting (higher pressure on near-win targets).
  - Watching payment: prefer `💰`, fallback `🔍`.

## 5) Performer
- Initial: `🔍2 💰1 ❤️6 📦0 👑1 🤴🏻1`
- Draw cost: `THEN / money-1 | stamina-1`
- Skill: requires wearing orange (`🤴🏻 >= 1`) before start.
  - Ask players to watch.
  - Each watcher first chooses to watch, then pays watch cost: `💰-1` or `🔍-2`.
  - After payment, watcher may choose to wear/take off one orange item.
  - Performer gains `💰+1` per watcher.
  - Success threshold: `>=2` watchers (unless event overrides to `1`).
  - Success: performer `❤️-2`, `⭐️+1`.
  - Fail: performer `❤️-1`.
- Win: `3` successful performances.
- Auto strategy (synced to game logic):
  - Turn choice: strong perform-first preference once perform is available.
  - Event target choice: strong threat-focused target selection.
  - Watching behavior: high watch participation.
  - Watching payment: prefer `💰`, fallback `🔍`.

## 6) Volunteer
- Initial: `🔍2 💰5 ❤️2 📦1 👑0 🤴🏻0`
- Draw cost: `OR / stamina-2 | stamina-1 + curiosity-1`
- Skill: choose target + help type; target may accept/refuse.
  - On accept: target `❤️+1`; if type is `photo`, target `🔍+1`.
  - Volunteer gains `⭐️+1`.
  - If target is Finn: Finn gains `1` assisted-buy chance.
- Win: `3` successful helps.

---

## Events (Cards 1-20)

## Card 1: Orange Crown
- Global: Drawer gains `👑+1`.
- Finn: wear it at no cost.
- Vendor: orange item stall price `+2` (stackable).
- Tourist: gift to anyone, then attempt photo.
  - For this card, if gifting to Finn, Finn auto-wears.
- Food Vendor: if already wearing orange, future food cost `x2` and food effect `x2`.
- Performer: wear it, then immediate perform; success threshold becomes `1` audience for that perform.

## Card 2: DOESN'T FIT RIGHT
- Global: `Targets` are all players with lowest `🔍` (including drawer).
  - Each target gains `🔍+1`.
  - Drawer gains extra `🔍+1` (can stack to `+2` if also a target).
- Finn: if wearing orange, gain `👑+1`.
- Vendor: trade with each non-self target (cannot refuse).
- Food Vendor: supply each non-self target (no refusal).
- Performer: if player count > 1, gain `⭐️+1`; else start performance.
- Tourist: photo each non-self target.
  - If target has orange (worn/held) or target is Finn: cannot refuse.
  - Otherwise ask consent one by one.

## Card 3: Orange scarf
- Global: Drawer gains `👑+1`.
- Finn: wear it at no cost.
- Vendor: keep it in stall (inventory).
- Food Vendor: gift to any player, then gain `❤️+1`.
- Tourist: gift to any player, force target to wear it, then photo (cannot refuse).
- Performer:
  - If not wearing, wear it.
  - If already wearing, start perform with `1` audience requirement.

## Card 4: All IN Orange
- Global (all): all players gain `🔍+1`.
- Baseline role effect: drawer gains `👑+1`.
- Tourist: attempt a photo.
- Food Vendor: start supply now, this supply grants fixed `❤️+1` effect.
- Vendor: all trade prices `x2` (stackable).
- Performer: start performance now.
  - If already wearing orange, gain `⭐️+1` regardless of performance outcome.

## Card 5: TOO CROWDED
- Global (drawer only): `❤️-1, 🔍+1`.
- Finn: spend `1❤️` -> `👑+1`.
- Tourist: pay `2📦`, then attempt `1` photo.
- Food Vendor: supply now with no stamina cost.
- Vendor: choose one:
  - Wear an orange item.
  - Start trade (`📦` price `*2` for this trade flow).
  - Start trade (`👑` cannot be refused).
- Performer: perform now.
  - If wearing orange, success threshold is `1` audience; else normal threshold.

## Card 6: Pop-up Stall
- Global (drawer only): gain `📦+1`.
- Finn: choose a target with `👑`, force swap `1📦 -> 1👑` (cannot refuse).
- Vendor: start trade, `📦` only, cannot refuse.
- Tourist: spend `1📦` -> `🔍+1`.
- Food Vendor: spend `1📦` -> `💰+1`.
- Performer: spend `1📦` -> `👑+1`.

## Card 7: quick Swap
- Global: choose another player as target.
- Finn: if `🔍>=6`, swap any one own item (`📦` or `👑`) for `1👑` from target (cannot refuse).
- Food Vendor: offer swap `1📦` for `1👑`.
  - If refused, target pays food vendor `💰+1`.
  - If target cannot pay that `💰1`, target cannot refuse.
- Vendor: offer swap `1📦` for `1👑`.
  - If refused, target pays vendor `💰+1`.
  - If target cannot pay that `💰1`, target cannot refuse.
- Performer: swap any one item with target (both must have at least one item), then gain `❤️+2`.
- Tourist: offer swap `1📦` for `1👑`; if refused, may attempt a photo on that target.

## Card 8: LOOKS INTERESTING
- Global: choose `1` target player, target gains `🔍+1`.
- Finn: if `🔍>=6`, swap one own item (`📦` or `👑`) for target `1👑` (cannot refuse).
- Performer: if target has both `👑` and `🤴🏻`, start performance immediately.
  - Target must join as watcher.
  - No stamina cost for this performance.
- Tourist: photo the target (cannot refuse).
- Vendor: trade with target (cannot refuse).
- Food Vendor: supply target (cannot refuse); if successful, gain `⭐️+1`.

## Card 9: IMPROVISED PERFORMANCE
- Global (all): each player chooses whether to Watch.
  - Each watcher gains `❤️+2`.
- Finn: if Finn watched, gain `👑+1`.
- Performer: start a performance.
  - If watching crowd has `2+` players, use that crowd directly for this performance.
- Tourist: attempt one photo of the watching crowd, and record `1` photo success when completed.
- Vendor: trade with the watching crowd.
- Food Vendor: supply to the watching crowd.

## Card 10: JOIN THE ACT?
- Global (drawer only): gain `🔍+1`.
- Finn: gain `👑+1` and `❤️+1`.
- Performer: start a performance now, with no stamina cost.
- Tourist: attempt `1` photo; if refused, gain `🔍+2`.
- Food Vendor: wear `1` orange item if available.
- Vendor: wear `1` orange item if available.

## Card 11: NONSTOP APPLAUSE
- Global (drawer only): gain `❤️+1` and `🔍+1`.
- Finn: choose one:
  - gain `👑+1`, or
  - wear `1` orange item.
- Performer: start a performance, and gain `+1` performance success immediately.
- Tourist: attempt `1` photo of the performer.
  - If performer has no `📦`, performer cannot refuse this photo.
- Vendor: start a trade.
  - If vendor has or is wearing orange item, this trade flow uses `price x2`.
- Food Vendor: start a supply.
  - If food vendor has or is wearing orange item, this supply uses `food price x2`.

## Card 12: PULLED ON STAGE
- Global: choose `1` target player, target gains `📦+1`.
- Finn: ask target to help Finn wear `1` orange item (if Finn has orange item).
- Performer: start a performance; target must watch.
- Tourist: attempt `1` photo of target.
  - If refused, target `❤️-1`.
- Vendor: trade with target.
  - Target can't refuse.
- Food Vendor: start supply to target.
  - If refused, food vendor `❤️+2`, and target `❤️-1`.

## Card 13: Photos Everwhere
- Global (all): all players choose whether to participate.
  - Each participant gains `🔍+1`.
- Finn: if Finn participates, gain extra `🔍+2`.
- Food Vendor: supply to target (cannot refuse); if successful, gain `⭐+1`.
- Performer: if target has `👑` and `🤴🏻`, start perform with no cost; target must join.
- Vendor: trade with target (cannot refuse).
- Tourist: if `2+` players participate, attempt `1` photo.

## Card 14: TAKE ME A PHOTO?
- Global: choose another player as target; target gains `🔍+1`.
- Finn: target gives `1` orange item (`👑`) to Finn if target has one.
- Food Vendor: start supply to target; target can't refuse.
- Performer: start perform; target must watch.
- Vendor: trade with target.
  - If target has no worn orange (`🤴🏻`), target can't refuse.
- Tourist: attempt `1` photo of target; can't be refused.

## Card 15: Secretly filming
- Global: choose another player as target; target gains `🔍+2`.
- Finn: choose one:
  - Get `1` common item (`📦+1`).
  - Wear `1` orange item.
- Food Vendor: provide `1` food to target.
  - If target has unworn orange (`👑`), target can't refuse this supply.
  - Target pays `1` orange item (`👑`) if target has one.
  - Food Vendor gains `⭐+1`.
- Vendor: swap with target (cannot refuse).
- Performer: choose one:
  - Get `1` common item (`📦+1`).
  - Swap with target (cannot refuse).
- Tourist: take `1` photo of target.
  - Target cannot refuse, and target gains `💰+2`.

## Card 16: PERFECT SHOT
- Global (drawer only): gain `💰+1`.
- Finn: choose one:
  - Get `1` orange item (`👑+1`).
  - Wear `1` orange item.
- Food Vendor: supply now.
  - Food effect this round is `❤️+2`.
- Vendor: choose one own item to sell to Tourist (cannot refuse).
- Performer: get `❤️+2`.
- Tourist: take `1` photo; target can't refuse.
  - Target gets `1` common item (`📦+1`) from photo.

## Card 17: LET'S GRAB A BITE
- Global: choose another player as target; target gains `📦+2`.
- Finn: gain `🔍+2`.
- Food Vendor: start supply with no cost; target can't refuse.
- Performer: wear `1` orange item.
- Vendor: trade to target; target can't refuse.
- Tourist: gain `💰+1` and `🔍+1`.

## Card 18: SMELLS DELICIOUS
- Global (drawer only): pay `💰-1`, gain `👑+1`.
- Finn: choose one:
  - Pay `🔍-1`, get `👑+1`.
  - Pay `🔍-2`, wear `1` orange item.
- Food Vendor: pay `❤️-1`, get `📦+1`.
- Performer: pay `🔍-1`, get `📦+1`.
- Vendor: start trade with one player.
  - If vendor is wearing orange, target can't refuse.
- Tourist: pay `👑-1`, take `1` photo, cannot be refused.

## Card 19: LONG LINE
- Global: choose another player as target; target and drawer gain `❤️+2`.
- Finn: ask target to give Finn `1` orange item and help Finn wear it; can't be refused.
- Food Vendor: start supply to target; target can't refuse.
- Performer: wear `1` orange item.
- Vendor: trade to target; target can't refuse.
  - After trade, target pays `❤️-1`.
- Tourist: ask target to wear `1` orange item, then take `1` photo; can't be refused.

## Card 20: LAST SERVING
- Global: all players gain `💰+1`; Finn gains `❤️+1`.
- Finn: wear `1` orange item with no cost.
- Food Vendor: start a swap with target; target can't refuse.
- Performer: choose one:
  - Pay `👑-1`, get `📦+1`.
  - Pay `👑-1`, get `❤️+1`.
- Vendor: trade to target; target can't refuse.
  - Target pays `👑-1` to vendor after trade.
- Tourist: ask target to wear `1` orange item, then take `1` photo; can't be refused.
